trifecta of activity going on.

00:02:47.070 --> 00:02:51.480
But today's event is not only one
of the Benjamin Botkin lectures,

00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:55.840
it's also part of a year-long
celebration of Alan Lomax

00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:58.800
on the occasion of the
centennial of his birth.

00:02:58.800 --> 00:03:00.660
So happy birthday.

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:07.370
The Alan Lomax collection is one
of ASC's largest most prestigious

00:03:07.370 --> 00:03:09.880
and most celebrated collections.

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:13.990
And although Lomax is -- most
of his work is well known,

00:03:13.990 --> 00:03:16.790
certainly particularly
the Anglo-American

00:03:16.790 --> 00:03:21.500
and African-American work, there
are other aspects of his collecting

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:24.290
and his scholarship that
is not as well known.

00:03:24.290 --> 00:03:29.480
And this is particularly true of
his work on dance and dance theory,

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:33.700
to which he devoted a significant
portion of his later career.

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:37.380
The study of dance is formalized
culturally, conditioned,

00:03:37.380 --> 00:03:42.070
communicative behavior based on
researching the diversity of dance

00:03:42.070 --> 00:03:45.760
and it's relationship to different
cultures throughout the world,

00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.870
a field which he christened
choreometrics has been

00:03:48.870 --> 00:03:50.960
unduly neglected.

00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:55.520 position:56%
As was true with so many important
researchers, Alan Lomax did not work

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:59.940
in isolation and indeed throughout
his entire career he worked

00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:03.330
with a range of collaborators
and colleagues.

00:04:03.330 --> 00:04:06.230
And choreometrics is no different.

00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:11.600
Lomax launched the enormous
choreometrics project in 1965

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:16.660
with collaborators Irmgard
Bartenieff and Forrestine Paulay.

