00:51:27.330 --> 00:51:32.600
to reduce the number of
parameters on the coding sheet

00:51:32.600 --> 00:51:38.130 position:56%
so maybe there could be 40 different
parameters instead of the four pages

00:51:38.130 --> 00:51:41.550
of codes that we were
putting in for awhile.

00:51:41.550 --> 00:51:44.570
He was trying to -- working
with you also, Forrestine --

00:51:44.570 --> 00:51:48.360
trying to find what were the
most essential characteristics

00:51:48.360 --> 00:51:52.990
that could speak to the essence of
the dance of the use of the body,

00:51:52.990 --> 00:51:57.690
the social organization or the
relationship to the audience,

00:51:57.690 --> 00:51:59.520
the dynamics of the movement.

00:51:59.520 --> 00:52:02.550
What could be the minimum number
of variables that you could look at

00:52:02.550 --> 00:52:05.550
and still get something
meaningful from it?

00:52:05.550 --> 00:52:06.850
&gt;&gt; Forrestine Paulay:

00:52:06.850 --> 00:52:09.560
He was actually doing factor
analysis work on that.

00:52:09.560 --> 00:52:13.180
So it would not -- it
wasn't just by looking

00:52:13.180 --> 00:52:15.940
and saying well let's
